---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Iran Conflict Tracker">
  <div class="about-page">
    <a class="about-back" href="/iran-conflict-tracker/">&larr; Dashboard</a>

    <article class="about-content">
      <h1>About This Project</h1>

      <section>
        <h2>What is this?</h2>
        <p>
          The Iran Conflict Tracker is an open-source intelligence dashboard that aggregates, visualizes, and contextualizes publicly available information about the 2026 Iran&#8211;US/Israel conflict.
          It combines data from official sources, major news outlets, research institutions, and OSINT feeds into a single, navigable interface&mdash;including an interactive 2D theater map and a 3D globe.
        </p>
        <p>
          Data is updated nightly via AI-assisted analysis of open sources. Every data point is tagged with a source tier (from official/primary to unverified) so readers can assess reliability at a glance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Disclaimer &amp; No Guarantees</h2>
        <p>
          This dashboard is provided on a <strong>best-effort basis</strong>, with no warranties of any kind&mdash;express or implied. Specifically:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Information may be <strong>incomplete, delayed, or inaccurate</strong>. Conflict data is inherently uncertain and contested.</li>
          <li>AI-assisted updates may introduce errors. All AI outputs are validated against schemas, but factual accuracy cannot be guaranteed.</li>
          <li>This project does <strong>not</strong> endorse any political position, government narrative, or military action.</li>
          <li>Nothing here constitutes professional intelligence analysis, legal advice, or journalistic reporting.</li>
          <li>The dashboard presents <strong>multiple perspectives</strong> (Western, Middle Eastern, Eastern, International) without claiming any single perspective is correct.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Use this information at your own discretion. When in doubt, consult primary sources directly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How Data Gets Updated</h2>
        <p>
          Every day at 6:00 AM UTC, a fully automated pipeline searches the web for the latest conflict developments and updates the dashboard. No human touches the data between updates.
        </p>

        <div class="pipeline-flow">
          <div class="pipeline-step">
            <div class="step-icon">&#128339;</div>
            <div class="step-label">Cron Trigger</div>
            <div class="step-detail">6 AM UTC daily<br/>GitHub Actions scheduler</div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="pipeline-step">
            <div class="step-icon">&#129302;</div>
            <div class="step-label">AI Web Search</div>
            <div class="step-detail">Claude Code searches open sources across 4 poles<br/>(Western, Middle Eastern, Eastern, International)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="pipeline-step">
            <div class="step-icon">&#128203;</div>
            <div class="step-label">Schema Validation</div>
            <div class="step-detail">Zod schemas enforce types, coordinate bounds,<br/>date formats, and required fields</div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="pipeline-step">
            <div class="step-icon">&#128257;</div>
            <div class="step-label">Merge by ID</div>
            <div class="step-detail">New entries added, existing updated<br/>Additive only &mdash; data is never deleted</div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="pipeline-step">
            <div class="step-icon">&#9989;</div>
            <div class="step-label">JSON Validation</div>
            <div class="step-detail">All files checked for valid JSON<br/>Invalid data blocks the commit</div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="pipeline-step">
            <div class="step-icon">&#128640;</div>
            <div class="step-label">Build &amp; Deploy</div>
            <div class="step-detail">Astro static build with Zod cross-field checks<br/>Deployed to GitHub Pages</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="pipeline-caption">
          Source: <a href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker/blob/main/.github/workflows/update-data.yml" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">update-data.yml</a> and <a href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker/blob/main/.github/workflows/deploy.yml" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">deploy.yml</a> &mdash; the full pipeline is open source and auditable.
        </p>

        <div class="tradeoffs">
          <div class="tradeoff-col benefits">
            <h3>Benefits</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Fully automated</strong> &mdash; updates run 365 days/year with no human intervention</li>
              <li><strong>Multi-pole sourcing</strong> &mdash; AI is instructed to seek Western, Middle Eastern, Eastern, and International perspectives on every event</li>
              <li><strong>Schema-enforced</strong> &mdash; coordinate bounds, time formats, required fields, and cross-field constraints are validated at both ingestion and build time</li>
              <li><strong>Additive-only</strong> &mdash; merge-by-ID pattern prevents data loss; diff guards block suspicious array shrinkage</li>
              <li><strong>Transparent</strong> &mdash; every update is a Git commit, every workflow run is public, every schema is auditable</li>
              <li><strong>Source tiered</strong> &mdash; every claim tagged Tier 1&ndash;4 so readers can gauge reliability themselves</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="tradeoff-col limitations">
            <h3>Limitations</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>AI hallucination risk</strong> &mdash; the AI may generate plausible-sounding but incorrect details, especially for casualty figures or attributed quotes</li>
              <li><strong>No human editorial review</strong> &mdash; there is no journalist or analyst verifying each update before it goes live</li>
              <li><strong>Source access gaps</strong> &mdash; paywalled, classified, or non-English sources may be missed or underrepresented</li>
              <li><strong>Latency</strong> &mdash; updates run once daily; breaking developments may take up to 24 hours to appear</li>
              <li><strong>Schema &#8800; truth</strong> &mdash; validation ensures data is structurally correct, not factually correct</li>
              <li><strong>No build failure alerts</strong> &mdash; if a nightly update fails, the site serves stale data with no notification (planned fix)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Help Us Get It Right</h2>
        <p>
          This dashboard is only as accurate as its sources and the AI that processes them. If you spot an error, a missing event, a miscategorized source, or a factual inaccuracy&mdash;please let us know.
        </p>
        <div class="contribute-grid">
          <a class="contribute-card" href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker/issues/new?template=bug_report.md&title=[Fact+Check]+..." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="contribute-icon">&#128269;</span>
            <strong>Report an Inaccuracy</strong>
            <span>Flag incorrect data, wrong dates, misattributed sources, or disputed figures</span>
          </a>
          <a class="contribute-card" href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker/issues/new?template=feature_request.md&title=[Feature]+..." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="contribute-icon">&#128161;</span>
            <strong>Suggest a Feature</strong>
            <span>Propose new data sections, visualization ideas, or UX improvements</span>
          </a>
          <a class="contribute-card" href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker/issues/new?title=[Source]+..." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="contribute-icon">&#128240;</span>
            <strong>Submit a Source</strong>
            <span>Point us to a primary source, OSINT feed, or underrepresented perspective</span>
          </a>
          <a class="contribute-card" href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="contribute-icon">&#128187;</span>
            <strong>Contribute Code</strong>
            <span>The codebase is open source &mdash; PRs are welcome</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Inspiration</h2>
        <p>
          The 3D intelligence globe was inspired by the work at <strong>Spatial Intelligence</strong>&mdash;specifically their piece
          <a href="https://www.spatialintelligence.ai/p/the-intelligence-monopoly-is-over" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">&ldquo;The Intelligence Monopoly is Over&rdquo;</a>.
          Their vision of democratizing geospatial intelligence through accessible visualization was a driving motivation for this project.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Built With</h2>
        <div class="credits-grid">
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>Astro</strong>
            <span>Static site framework</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>React</strong>
            <span>Interactive island components</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>CesiumJS</strong>
            <span>3D globe visualization</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>Resium</strong>
            <span>React bindings for Cesium</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>Leaflet</strong>
            <span>2D interactive mapping</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>satellite.js</strong>
            <span>Satellite orbit propagation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>Zod</strong>
            <span>Schema validation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>TypeScript</strong>
            <span>Type-safe codebase</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>Anthropic Claude API</strong>
            <span>AI-assisted nightly data updates</span>
          </div>
          <div class="credit-item">
            <strong>OpenAI API</strong>
            <span>Alternate AI provider</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          This project is open source.
          <a href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/iran-conflict-tracker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub</a>&mdash;contributions, bug reports, and feature suggestions are welcome.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .about-back {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .about-back:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-color: var(--border-light);
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  .about-content h1 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-content ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }
  .about-content ul li {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .about-content ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.75rem;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--accent-red);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .about-content a {
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .about-content a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent-blue);
  }

  .credits-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .credit-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .credit-item strong {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .credit-item span {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  /* ── Pipeline flow ── */
  .pipeline-flow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .pipeline-step {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 110px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 0.6rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .step-icon {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .step-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .step-detail {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .pipeline-arrow {
    color: var(--accent-red);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .pipeline-caption {
    font-size: 0.75rem !important;
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* ── Tradeoffs ── */
  .tradeoffs {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .tradeoff-col h3 {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .benefits h3 { color: var(--accent-green); }
  .limitations h3 { color: var(--accent-amber); }
  .tradeoff-col ul {
    margin: 0 !important;
  }
  .tradeoff-col li {
    font-size: 0.78rem !important;
    line-height: 1.6 !important;
    padding: 0.25rem 0 0.25rem 1.2rem !important;
  }
  .benefits li::before { background: var(--accent-green) !important; }
  .limitations li::before { background: var(--accent-amber) !important; }

  /* ── Contribute grid ── */
  .contribute-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .contribute-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    text-decoration: none !important;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    border-bottom: none !important;
  }
  .contribute-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-light);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .contribute-icon {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }
  .contribute-card strong {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .contribute-card span:last-child {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-page { padding: 1.5rem 1rem 3rem; }
    .about-content h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    .credits-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pipeline-flow { flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch; }
    .pipeline-arrow { transform: rotate(90deg); text-align: center; margin: 0; }
    .tradeoffs { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .contribute-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
